cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks related to object detection and segmentation, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also proposes a novel neural network architecture for this task, which involves feature separation and contextual reasoning, indicating a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of stripe convolution, which is a technique commonly used in robotics and control systems (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of occlusion, which is a common issue in computer graphics and computer vision (cs.CR).
